race.comment: MANNERHEIM (8) presents third up for the Waller barn and will be tough to beat stepping up to the middle distance. He went close this track/trip behind stablemate ICHIBAN before spelling, and Ben Thompson is a key jockey switch. ICHIBAN (3) is third up out of the same race and is also ready to fire. He gets in well with the 3kg claim and is sure to go close. Wary of the Vandyke-trained WOWZINO (5) building on the heavily bet win at the Sunshine Coast over 1800m. This is a step up but he has plenty of scope for improvement and Maloney sticking aboard is a decent push for his chance. The Geran-trained pair COUNTER (9) and MARENARO (1) come out of the same race and Eagle Farm and can't entirely be ruled out. They're in the trifectas at least.
